    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology/Warning"/>
    <ex:description>Adverse effects experienced at doses higher than recommended are similar to those seen at normal doses. Symptoms of a macrolide antibiotic overdose typically include reversible hearing loss, severe nausea, vomiting, and diarrhea. In case of an overdose, administration of medicinal charcoal is recommended, along with general symptomatic treatment and supportive measures as needed.</ex:description>
